---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="week 12 — the ratio is usually like this" description="four reads on ai tooling. one validated what i already do. one taught me something i figured out weeks ago. one actually changed a workflow.">
  <div class="space-y-6">
    <div class="font-mono text-xs text-faint mb-4">
      <a href="/reading" class="text-spice hover:underline">reading</a> <span class="text-faint">/</span> week 12
    </div>

    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-normal animate-fade-up">the ratio is usually like this</h1>

    <div class="essay mt-10 animate-fade-up delay-1">
      <p>read four things this week about ai tooling</p>

      <p class="mt-6">one validated what i already do</p>
      <p>one taught me something i figured out weeks ago</p>
      <p>one actually changed a workflow</p>
      <p class="text-dim">one was a good primer on the industry</p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-spice">the ratio tells you something</p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>boris cherny — the guy who built claude code — talking about how he builds with it</p>

      <p class="mt-6">recognized my own workflow in his approach</p>
      <p class="text-spice">three terminals. three contexts. one product.</p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-dim">felt less like learning and more like confirmation</p>

      <p class="mt-6"><a href="https://newsletter.pragmaticengineer.com/p/building-claude-code-with-boris-cherny" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-water hover:underline">Building Claude Code with Boris Cherny →</a></p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>mihail eric talking about a new era of learning software engineering — juniors starting with ai from day one</p>

      <p class="mt-6">the framing is solid</p>
      <p>but when you've already built a governance layer because your agents were lying to each other</p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-dim">it feels like catching up</p>

      <p class="mt-6"><a href="https://youtube.com/watch?v=wEsjK3Smovw" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-water hover:underline">From Writing Code to Managing Agents →</a></p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>the figma piece was different</p>

      <p class="mt-6">designers update spacing in figma</p>
      <p>engineers don't know</p>
      <p class="text-crimson">drift compounds silently for weeks</p>

      <p class="mt-6">now it's one prompt to sync production code with the design file</p>
      <p class="text-spice">that's not incremental. that kills an entire class of bug</p>

      <p class="mt-6"><a href="https://lennysnewsletter.com/p/from-figma-to-claude-code-and-back" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-water hover:underline">From Figma to Claude Code and back →</a></p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>ben thompson's agents over bubbles — <span class="text-gold">good primer on where the ai industry actually sits right now</span></p>

      <p class="mt-6">not a hot take. just clean structural analysis of who's building what and why the agent layer matters more than the model layer</p>

      <p class="mt-6"><a href="https://stratechery.com/2026/agents-over-bubbles" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-water hover:underline">Agents Over Bubbles →</a></p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>the pattern across all four:</p>

      <p class="mt-6">most ai content is still framing the problem</p>
      <p>the value is in the artifacts that skip the framing</p>
      <p class="text-spice">and just solve the workflow</p>

      <p class="mt-6">figma mcp doesn't explain why syncing matters</p>
      <p class="text-dim">it just syncs</p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p class="text-gold">a filter for what's worth reading:</p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-spice">did it change something i do tomorrow</p>
      <p>or did it describe something i did last week</p>

      <p class="mt-6">most weeks the ratio is 1:4</p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-spice">the one is worth the four</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 pt-6 border-t border-border">
      <a href="/reading" class="text-spice hover:underline">← back to reading</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .essay p {
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
</style>
